Bank of Africa's Ugandan Unit Says Full-Year Net Income Increased by 9.9%

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-03-11T05:59:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/bank-of-africa-s-ugandan-unit-says-full-year-net-income-increased-by-9-9-.html
Bank of Africa Uganda Ltd. said net
income for the 12 months to Dec. 31 increased 9.9 percent to
3.65 billion shillings ($1.53 million) as customer deposits and
loans grew.  Deposits by customers rose 38 percent to 220.6 billion
shillings during the period, the Kampala-based lender said in an
advertisement published in the New Vision newspaper today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  